Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and slice the @Red Onion{1/2}(halved, peeled and sliced) as thinly as you can.

In a small #bowl{}, combine the sliced onion, @Red Wine Vinegar{12%ml} and @Sugar{1%tsp}. Add a pinch of @salt{pinch}, mix together and set aside to pickle.

Cut the @Medium Tomato{1}(cut into 1cm chunks). Add to a medium bowl and stir in the @Olive Oil{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt and @pepper. Set aside.

Heat a large saucepan with a tight-fitting lid on medium-high heat.

Add the @Slow Cooked British Chicken{290%g} along with the juices from the packet.

Simmer on low with the lid on until tender enough to shred with a #fork{}, ~{10-15%mins}. IMPORTANT: Ensure the chicken is piping hot throughout.

In the meantime, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%g}.

Once the chicken is tender, remove the lid and shred the meat.

Stir through the @Chipotle Paste{20%g}, @BBQ Sauce{96%g} and @Butter{20%g}. Season with @salt and @pepper, then remove from the heat.

> Add less chipotle paste if you'd prefer things milder.

When everything's ready, add the @Wild Rocket{20%g} to the bowl of tomatoes and toss to coat in the dressing.

Share the rice between your #serving bowls{} and top with the pulled chicken.

Sprinkle with the cheese.

Serve the pickled onion alongside.

Pour the remaining pickling liquid into the salad and toss to coat. Add the salad on the side.

Enjoy!